{"questionId":"22443280","questionHtml":"<p>Find the two possible sizes of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math>, giving your answers in degrees.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to use the sine rule to find&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>25</mn><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mn>28</mn><mo>°</mo></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>50</mn><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></mstyle><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mn>69</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8748</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>°</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;or&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mn>110</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>125</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>°</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for each value.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>attempt to find at least one possible angle for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mn>180</mn><mo>°</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>28</mn><mo>°</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>69</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8748</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>°</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mn>180</mn><mo>°</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>28</mn><mo>°</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>110</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>125</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>°</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>82</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1251</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>°</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>41</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8748</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>°</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>OAB</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>82</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>°</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>41</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>°</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to use the cosine rule to find <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>OB</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>25</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mn>50</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>OB</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mn>50</mn></mfenced><mfenced><mi>OB</mi></mfenced><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mn>28</mn><mo>°</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>OB</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>52</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7491</mn><mo>…</mo></math>&nbsp; or&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>35</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5455</mn><mo>…</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to use the sine rule to find&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>25</mn><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mn>28</mn><mo>°</mo></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>OB</mi><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></mstyle><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>82</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1251</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>°</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>41</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8748</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>°</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>82</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>°</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>41</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>°</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[5 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22443280","referenceCode":"24M.2.SL.TZ1.9ai","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the two possible sizes of OA^B, giving your answers in degrees.","paper":"